{"id": "34", "question": "In Black Myth Wukong, character A, shown in this picture, died in a fight with another character B, who also bit character A. How many wheels does character B have?", "observations": [{"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Just a moment...\nPAGE_TEXT: Just a moment... Enable JavaScript and cookies to continue", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_0", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: How to Reach Chapter 5 Secret Area in Black Myth: Wukong\nPAGE_TEXT: How to Reach Chapter 5 Secret Area in Black Myth: Wukong Menu Sign in Sign in now Close Databases Game News Reviews Previews Game Guides Features Interviews Lists Videos Sign in Newsletter Array Copyright © 2026 hardcoregamer.com --> Black Myth: Wukong Latest Armor Bosses Curious & Relics Weapons Spirits Skills Skills Foundation Staff Stance Mysticism Alteration More Black Myth: Wukong Persona 5 Royal Elden Ring Stardew Valley Dragon's Dogma 2 Helldivers 2 Palworld Baldur's Gate 3 Stalker 2 Close How to Reach Chapter 5 Secret Area in Black Myth: Wukong By Parker Green Published Sep 3, 2024, 6:46 PM EDT Parker Green is a writer and creator from Los Angeles, CA, and a graduate from California State University, Los Angeles with a Bachelor's Degree in Television, Film, and Media Studies. Parker is a newcomer to the field of games journalism, but is already making big strides in his career by previewing games, attending industry events, and expanding his portfolio. Always on the search for the next great game to play, his favorite part about writing for Hardcore Gamer is being able to introduce readers to new games and content to experience. Additionally, Parker is passionate about creative direction, and spends much of his time discussing game design, industry trends, and pop culture. He's currently producing a new web series called \"Indie Games You Should Be Playing\" which aims to highlight lesser-known projects made by independent or small developers. In addition to playing video games, Parker spends his time voice acting and screenwriting, as well as making music under the pseudonym Mr. Sparkler. Sign in to your Hardcore Gamer account Add Us On Jump links Jump Links Defeat the Pale-Axe Stalwart Defeat the First Two Carts Find the Third and Fourth Cart Defeat the Fifth Cart Enter the Bishui Cave follow Follow followed Followed Like Like Thread Log in Here is a fact-based summary of the story contents: Try something different: Show me the facts Explain it like I’m 5 Give me a lighthearted recap Continuing our series of guides on how to reach Black Myth: Wukong 's various secret areas, we're taking a look at how to reach the Bishui Cave area in the Flaming Mountains region. Related Black Myth: Wukong | How to Reach Chapter 4 Secret Area How to find the Purple Cloud Mountain in the Webbed Hollow! Posts By Parker Green This is one of the longer secret area questlines, but thankfully, most of the tasks required occur on the normal path of progression through the level. If you can't find a boss listed below, you may have already defeated them! Defeat the Pale-Axe Stalwart Just after the Ashen Pass I shrine, you'll discover a battle taking place. Defeat all the enemies here, as well as the Pale-Axe Stalwart mini-boss. Upon his defeat, he will kneel down and recognize you, becoming non-hostile and opening up the ability for dialogue. Exhaust all of his dialogue options, in which he will task you with finding and destroying five carts. Defeat the First Two Carts From the Pale-Axe Stalwart, head to the left along the normal path to a stairway that leads up to the Brown-Iron Cart. Defeat this boss (we recommend using the raised platform on the right to get behind the cart, avoiding his breath attacks) and activate the shrine behind it. Next, continue along the path across the bridge and through the caves, past where you fight the Father of Stones. You will eventually arrive at another bridge, which will initiate the Gray-Bronze Cart battle. During the fight, take cover in the recesses of the rocky wall when the cart attacks, popping out when the animation ends to attack. Once you have defeated the Gray-Bronze Cart (it may take some time), head back to the Pale-Axe Stalwart. The Pale-Axe Stalwart can now be found on a cliffside close by to where you first found him. Exhaust all of his dialogue options again, then continue through the level until you reach the Emerald Hall shrine. Find the Third and Fourth Cart The third cart has already bee", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_1", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Black Myth Wukong | How to Complete the Pale Axe Stalwart Element Carts Quest Chapter 5 - YouTube\nPAGE_TEXT: Black Myth Wukong | How to Complete the Pale Axe Stalwart Element Carts Quest Chapter 5 - YouTube About Press Copyright Contact us Creator Advertise Developers Terms Privacy Policy & Safety How YouTube works Test new features © 2026 Google LLC", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_2", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}], "stats": {"n_source_urls": 3, "n_image_urls": 1, "n_observations": 3}}
