{"id": "38", "question": "There is a game character who appears in a game released in 2024, which features the character shown in the picture as its protagonist. This particular game character is located on the back of a turtle and is discovered while fishing. He is the third in a storyline featuring four enemies. The question is: what are the colors of the two gems on his weapon?", "observations": [{"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Cyan Loong - Black Myth: Wukong Guide - IGN\nPAGE_TEXT: Cyan Loong - Black Myth: Wukong Guide - IGN Focus Reset Skip to content Black Myth: Wukong Guide Start tracking progress Create a free account or Log in. Find in guide Task Search Checklists Interactive Maps Chapter 3 Boss List Chapter 3 Boss List Macaque Chief Kang-Jin Loong Captain Lotus-Vision Captain Wise-Voice Kang-Jin Star Cyan Loong Chen Loong Apramana Bat Non-White Lang-Li-Guhh-Lang Non-Able Old Ginseng Guai Green-Capped Martialist Captain Void-Illusion Captain Kalpa-Wave Monk from the Sea Non-Void Non-Pure Yellowbrow Chi Tiger Back To Top Black Myth: Wukong Guide Guide Checklists Maps Task Search Task Search Checklists Guides Markers Videos Sort and Filter No Results Checklists New Checklist All Lists My Checklists All Story Completion Bosses and Enemies Collectibles Weapons and Gear Transformations Equippable Consumables Locations Achievements and Trophies Story Completion Main Quests Bosses and Enemies Bosses Collectibles Key Items Weapons and Gear Weapons Weapons and Gear Armor and Unique Gear Weapons and Gear Vessels Transformations Transformation Spells Equippable Gourds Equippable Drinks Equippable Soaks Collectibles Spirits Collectibles Luojia Fragrant Vines Collectibles Awaken Wine Worms Collectibles Curios Consumables Celestial Pills Consumables Consumable Items Locations Meditation Spots Achievements and Trophies Achievements and Trophies All Lists My Checklists How creative can you get with your first free checklist? Create a free account All Interactive Maps and Locations Cyan Loong By Brendan Graeber , Echo Apsey , Lauren Harper , +13 more Updated : Sep 8, 2024 5:37am UTC View Interactive Map Cyan Loong is an optional secret Yaoguai King boss fight that you can encounter in Chapter 3 of Black Myth Wukong. Hiding on the far side of Turtle Island this frozen boss can't be activated until you obtain a Key Item in the previous chapter. Cyan Loong is one of four Loong Dragons that can be defeated to earn powerful weapon crafting materials. Rewards: Tridacna Pendant, Thunderbone, Loong Pearl x1, Refined Iron Sand x2, Mind Core x1 Where to Find Cyan Loong As an optional secret boss, Cyan Loong can be found once you reach Turtle Island on the Bitter Lake. You can find his frozen body apparently fishing off the side of the \"island\" by heading right from the Turtle Island Shrine. However, in order to activate this secret boss, you'll need to obtain the Loong Scales from the Yellow Wind Ridge in Chapter 2. Head through the Sandgate Village and defeat the King of Flowing Sand and his Second Rat Prince son. After defeating the pair (or only the son), head left from the boss arena and into the Valley of Despair. Once you arrive in the large covered valley area, keep to the left to find a large lower platform by a slightly rounded red wall lined with small statues. At this point, if you did not kill the King of Flowing Sand, he’ll summon his other son, the First Rat Prince — otherwise you can use the Pungent Flesh Chunk to summon him yourself. While fighting the First Rat Prince, you can lure him into performing one of his large slam attacks when facing the rounded wall, and it will cause a crack to appear in the wall. If you are unable to lure the boss into forming a crack in the wall, you can even do so yourself by hitting it with a very strong attack - we recommend the Wandering Wight’s Spirit Attack, or the Azure Dust Transformation Spell’s final attack. You can enter the crack in the wall, and on the other side you’ll find a chest containing the Loong Scales. With this item, you’ll be able to unlock the boss. Cyan Loong Boss Fight and Guide While the Cyan Loong is a bit smaller than Black Loong, he is much more ferocious, and can use his lightning powers to quickly deal double damage and tear you to pieces -- especially if you choose to face him after arriving on Turtle Island. You'll likely want to at least craft all three pieces of the Loongscale Armor unlocked by defeating Kang-Jin Star, as it boasts a reduction", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_0", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Just a moment...\nPAGE_TEXT: Just a moment... Enable JavaScript and cookies to continue", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_1", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}], "stats": {"n_source_urls": 2, "n_image_urls": 1, "n_observations": 2}}
