{"id": "40", "question": "In the game shown in the image, a treasure map can be found at this location, which initiates a questline. In the final mission of this questline, we can find six gold bars as a reward. In which casket, counting from bottom to top, are these six gold bars hidden?", "observations": [{"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Red Dead Redemption 2 Le Tresor Des Morts Treasure Map locations | Eurogamer.net\nPAGE_TEXT: Red Dead Redemption 2 Le Tresor Des Morts Treasure Map locations | Eurogamer.net Skip to main content 2026 Release Schedule Pokopia Pokédex Pokémon Champions Mystery Gift CD Ancient puzzle solutions Coin Master Board Adventure Free Energy Bizarre Lineage codes Supporters only Deals Buy eShop codes Eurogamer.net Go Support us Sign in / Create account Latest PC PlayStation Xbox Nintendo Tech News Reviews Videos Features Guides If you click on a link and make a purchase we may receive a small commission. Read our editorial policy . Home Guides Red Dead Redemption 2 Red Dead Redemption 2 Le Tresor Des Morts Treasure Map locations How to start - and complete - the pre-order exclusive treasure hunt. Guide by Jason Coles Contributor Updated on May 19, 2021 Follow Red Dead Redemption 2 Red Dead Redemption 2's Le Tresor Des Morts is a pre-order exclusive Treasure Map that's waiting to be discovering in the early part of the game. Of course, it's one thing knowing that this awaits you somewhere in the game, it's a very different thing actually finding it. That's why you'll need to know how to find the Le Tresor Des Morts location in order to find the treasure at the end - which, without spoiling specifics, is a very useful way to make money in Red Dead Redemption 2 nice and early. On this page: How to start Le Tresor Des Morts Treasure Map quest in Red Dead Redemption 2 Le Tresor Des Morts Map 1 Location Le Tresor Des Morts Map 2 location Le Tresor Des Morts treasure location For more help, our Red Dead Redemption 2 walkthrough explains the requirements for fully completing the game's many story missions. [4K HDR] Red Dead Redemption 2 HDR Fix Tested! Plus Graphics 'Downgrade' Analysis [4K HDR] Red Dead Redemption 2 HDR Fix Tested! Plus Graphics 'Downgrade' Analysis Watch on YouTube How to start Le Tresor Des Morts Treasure Map quest in Red Dead Redemption 2 Starting this treasure hunt requires you to have finished the mission Eastward Bound , which means you'll need to be in Chapter 2. Once you are, the good news is that you can complete this particular hunt with very little effort, all you need to know is where to find things. Le Tresor Des Morts Map 1 Location Just to the east of your camp in Horseshoe Overlook is a burned-out village called Limpany. Head over to the village, and you'll see that there are only two buildings still standing. Before you get the map, it's worth going inside the Sheriff's building and checking the lockbox under the desk inside, as you'll find a Gold Bar here. Once you've done that, head over to the other building and go inside, go into the left-hand cell and pick up the map to start this treasure hunt in earnest. You'll see that the map appears to be pointing to some kind of dock and then a tunnel of some sort. Well, it's tough to tell from this image alone, but we're off to a place called Saint Denis. Le Tresor Des Morts Map 2 location Getting to Saint Denis is actually very easy if you're willing to spend a small amount of money on a train ticket. While fast travelling in Red Dead Redemption 2 can be a little awkward, trains are available from the get-go and can take you to places you've never been. This includes Saint Denis. Simply head to a train station and buy a ticket there. Once you arrive, you'll need to head east to the point marked on the map. You want to head down the steps on the left and then stick to the wall on your right, drop into the water, and carry on until you find the metal doors on your right. Head inside until you reach the beam marked with an X, and you get the prompt to search. Do so, and you'll reveal the second map, although it's more of a clue with a doodle on the back. The clue is a riddle which says: Where the floods rise up, But the dead stay dry, And the colored light falls, When the sun's in the sky. There to your left you'll find our wealth, It's no good to us without our health. Solving this might lead you to the conclusion that you need to find a graveyard and a stain", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_0", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Just a moment...\nPAGE_TEXT: Just a moment... Enable JavaScript and cookies to continue", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_1", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Red Dead 2 Le Tresor Des Morts Treasure - Red Dead Redemption 2 Treasure Map - YouTube\nPAGE_TEXT: Red Dead 2 Le Tresor Des Morts Treasure - Red Dead Redemption 2 Treasure Map - YouTube About Press Copyright Contact us Creator Advertise Developers Terms Privacy Policy & Safety How YouTube works Test new features © 2026 Google LLC", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_2", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}], "stats": {"n_source_urls": 3, "n_image_urls": 1, "n_observations": 3}}
