{"id": "61", "question": "At the end of May 2024, an official promotional video featuring the car shown in the image was released. In the video, what is the license plate number of the red car?", "observations": [{"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Porsche 911 Carrera GTS | Porsche International\nPAGE_TEXT: Porsche 911 Carrera GTS | Porsche International 911 Carrera GTS Gasoline Coupé Cabriolet Targa GT Turbo Coupé Turbo Cabriolet Change model variant Configure Fuel consumption combined (model range): 10.7 – 10.1 l/100 km, CO₂-emissions combined (model range): 242 – 230 g/km . 3.0 s Acceleration 0 - 100 km/h with Sport Chrono Package 398 kW / 541 PS Power combined (kW) / Power combined (PS) 312 km/h Top speed View all technical details Feedback How helpful is the information on this page for you? Not helpful at all 1 2 3 4 5 Very helpful How could we improve this page for you? Send Feedback Feedback The one and always. Anyone who dreams of a Porsche usually has an image in their mind: the 911 has been the epitome of an exciting, powerful sports car with day-to-day usability for 60 years. Take a seat behind the wheel of the new 911 and become part of a unique community. T-Hybrid technology. The new T-Hybrid technology was derived from motorsport and combines emotive engine sound with outstanding performance. The significant increase in performance and the compact design of the lightweight T-Hybrid system also ensure an optimised power-to-weight ratio. Structure Function Performance Structure. Crucial to the high performance of the T-Hybrid system: the innovative main components. From the completely redeveloped 3.6-litre flat engine with electric exhaust turbocharger to the electric motor integrated in the PDK and the light, powerful traction battery. 3.6-litre flat-6 engine. This is what only a 911 sounds like: the new flat engine in the rear impresses with a classic 6-cylinder symphony, an increase in displacement from 3.0 to 3.6 l and further increased power output. Electric motor in the PDK. The electric motor integrated in the Porsche Doppelkupplung (PDK) offers high torque even at low speeds – and delivers its power directly and without delay. In Recuperation mode, it works as a dynamo. Electric exhaust turbocharger. The electric exhaust turbocharger ensures a faster increase in the performance-determining boost pressure and thus accelerated response behaviour. In Recuperation mode, energy from the exhaust stream is converted into electrical energy – similar to the Porsche 919 Hybrid developed for racing. High-voltage battery. The light and compact 400-volt traction battery has been optimised for maximum performance. It stores the energy gained through recuperation for new, unforgettable acceleration processes. Performance. System power: 398 kW (541 PS). Top speed: 312 km/h. With this technical data, a torque combined of 610 Nm and a sprint from 0 to 100 km/h in 3.0 s, it's highly unlikely that you will ever want to get out again. Fuel consumption combined (model range): 10.7 – 10.1 l/100 km, CO₂-emissions combined (model range): 242 – 230 g/km Highlights. Design. Clear lines and a muscular rear section create a much sharper character. On the GTS models, the newly designed front apron with striking vertical aerodynamic elements including adaptive air intake flaps provide a further distinctive visual feature. Headlights. Expressive and typically Porsche: the new Matrix LED main headlights, including all lighting functions such as the 4-point daytime running lights, increase the distinctive look of the 911 from afar with their lighting signature. Dynamics. The PASM sports chassis (-10 mm) with helper springs at the rear and the rear-axle steering increase the performance on the circuit as standard on the 911 Carrera GTS models. Driver experience. The instrument cluster puts the focus on the central rev counter with the classic five-tube view or the reduced Sport Chrono screen¹ as desired. Online services from Porsche Connect such as the My Porsche app in Apple CarPlay® offer maximum convenience. 1 Optionally available for 911 Carrera. App Centre. The App Centre offers an interactive experience with the ability to download your favourite apps from categories such as music and video streaming, gaming or news. Porsche Design custo", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_0", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Error 400 (Bad Request)!!1\nPAGE_TEXT: Error 400 (Bad Request)!!1 400. That’s an error. Your client has issued a malformed or illegal request. That’s all we know.", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_1", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}], "stats": {"n_source_urls": 2, "n_image_urls": 1, "n_observations": 2}}
