{"id": "60", "question": "This car was released in June 2022. At its June 2022 launch event, a scene was shown where four people were playing Switch together inside the car. In that scene, several game characters appeared on the roof-mounted screen. What is the second game character from the right?", "observations": [{"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Li L9 - Wikipedia\nPAGE_TEXT: Li L9 - Wikipedia Jump to content Main menu Main menu move to sidebar hide Navigation Main page Contents Current events Random article About Wikipedia Contact us Contribute Help Learn to edit Community portal Recent changes Upload file Special pages Search Search Appearance Donate Create account Log in Personal tools Donate Create account Log in Contents move to sidebar hide (Top) 1 First generation (2022) Toggle First generation (2022) subsection 1.1 Design and equipment 1.2 Powertrain 1.3 Update (2025) 2 Second generation (2026) Toggle Second generation (2026) subsection 2.1 Design 2.2 Features 2.3 Powertrain 3 Sales 4 References 5 External links Toggle the table of contents Li L9 10 languages Deutsch Español Հայերեն Italiano 日本語 한국어 Polski Русский Українська 中文 Edit links Article Talk English Read Edit View history Tools Tools move to sidebar hide Actions Read Edit View history General What links here Related changes Upload file Permanent link Page information Cite this page Get shortened URL Print/export Download as PDF Printable version In other projects Wikimedia Commons Wikidata item Appearance move to sidebar hide From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia Range-extender full-size luxury crossover SUV Motor vehicle Li L9 Overview Manufacturer Li Auto Production 2022–present Body and chassis Class Full-size luxury crossover SUV Body style 5-door SUV The Li L9 ( Chinese : 理想L9 ; pinyin : Lǐxiǎng L9 ; lit. 'ideal L9') is a range-extender luxury full-size crossover SUV produced by Chinese manufacturer Li Auto . It is the second vehicle from the manufacturer after the Li One , and also the first L-series model, which also includes the similar L8 , L7 and L6 . First generation (2022) [ edit ] Motor vehicle First generation Overview Model code X01 Production 2022–2026 (China) 2025–present (overseas) Assembly China: Changzhou, Jiangsu Designer Benjamin Baum, Gloria Ge Body and chassis Layout Front-engine, dual-motor, all-wheel drive Related Li L6 Li L7 Li L8 Powertrain Engine Gasoline range extender : 1.5 L L2E15M turbo I4 Electric motor Permanent magnet synchronous Power output 330 kW (440 hp) Transmission Single-speed gear reduction Battery 44.5 kWh NMC CATL 52.3 kWh NMC CATL Range 1,176 km (731 mi) Electric range 180–235 km (112–146 mi) (WLTP) Plug-in charging 75-90 kW DC Dimensions Wheelbase 3,105 mm (122.2 in) Length 5,218 mm (205.4 in) Width 1,998 mm (78.7 in) Height 1,800 mm (70.9 in) Curb weight 2,520–2,570 kg (5,556–5,666 lb) The first generation L9 was unveiled online on March 8, 2022 and officially launched on June 21, 2022 with the first vehicles delivered in China from August 2022. [ 1 ] Design and equipment [ edit ] The L9 is available with six seats in three rows. [ 1 ] The interior has a pair of two 4-millimetre (0.16 in) thick 15.7-inch wide screens. [ 2 ] Rear view Powertrain [ edit ] The vehicle can be described as a range extended vehicle . It has two electric motors: a 130-kilowatt (174 hp; 177 PS) motor in the front and a 200-kilowatt (268 hp; 272 PS) motor in the rear. It is also equipped with a front-mounted 1.5-litre turbocharged 4-cylinder petrol engine with a 65-litre (17.2 US gal; 14.3 imp gal) petrol tank capacity. The newer facelifted model has a gas tank of 55 litres (14.5 US gal; 12.1 imp gal). The petrol engine is a range extender for the electric motors; it does not directly power the wheels. Total power output is 240 kW (322 hp; 326 PS) and 530 N⋅m (54 kg⋅m; 391 lb⋅ft). The company claims a NEDC range of 1,315 kilometres (817 mi), and an electric-only NEDC range of 215 kilometres (134 mi). The L9 accelerates 0–100 km/h (0–62 mph) in 5.3 seconds. [ 3 ] Charging to 80% takes 40 minutes with a fast charger. [ clarification needed ] A full charge at 200V takes 6 hours. Battery capacity is 40.6 kWh, out of which 37.2 kWh is usable. [ citation needed ] Update (2025) [ edit ] The 2025 update for the L9 was revealed on May 8, 2025, with pre-orders opening the same day and deliveries beginning the followin", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_0", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: 中国家庭到底需要一辆什么样的车？理想L9给你答案。_哔哩哔哩_bilibili\nPAGE_TEXT: 中国家庭到底需要一辆什么样的车？理想L9给你答案。_哔哩哔哩_bilibili 首页 番剧 直播 游戏中心 会员购 漫画 赛事 投稿 中国家庭到底需要一辆什么样的车？理想L9给你答案。 3.2万 318 2022-06-22 02:46:21 未经作者授权，禁止转载 546 166 310 450 理想汽车2022夏季发布会，全程回顾。 欢迎收藏观看。 原创 发布会 理想汽车 发消息 创造移动的家，创造幸福的家。 关注 7.3万 接下来播放 自动连播 “你好，我是 Livis。” 理想汽车 41.0万 258 冰封之下，也能强力破冰。 理想汽车 31.1万 225 理想i6荣获中保研“5G”最高评级 理想汽车 4.5万 4 2026年第11周理想主动安全避免潜在事故18万次。 理想汽车 1.9万 0 理想汽车2026年3月交付41,053辆。 理想汽车 5.4万 1 这波理想好物我直接给到夯！ 理想汽车 2.0万 0 爆款计划，你选哪一个？（上） 理想汽车 1.7万 1 2026年第9周理想主动安全避免潜在事故18万次。 理想汽车 2.2万 0 理想i6荣获中汽研高分五星安全认证。 理想汽车 2.0万 3 2026年第10周理想主动安全避免潜在事故19万次。 理想汽车 2.4万 0 关上门，把喧嚣还给世界。 理想汽车 4.2万 0 断头路泊车不用慌，一键泊入超丝滑。 理想汽车 11.8万 10 展开 用AI为孩子创作优质内容 小窗 客服 顶部 赛事库 课堂 2021拜年纪", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_1", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Princess Daisy - Wikipedia\nPAGE_TEXT: Princess Daisy - Wikipedia Jump to content Main menu Main menu move to sidebar hide Navigation Main page Contents Current events Random article About Wikipedia Contact us Contribute Help Learn to edit Community portal Recent changes Upload file Special pages Search Search Appearance Donate Create account Log in Personal tools Donate Create account Log in Contents move to sidebar hide (Top) 1 Concept and creation 2 Appearances Toggle Appearances subsection 2.1 In video games 2.2 In other media 3 Reception 4 References Toggle the table of contents Princess Daisy 27 languages Ænglisc العربية Català Dansk Deutsch Esperanto Español فارسی Suomi Français עברית Bahasa Indonesia Italiano 日本語 한국어 Latina Nederlands Português Русский Simple English Svenska Türkçe Українська Tiếng Việt 吴语 ייִדיש 中文 Edit links Article Talk English Read Edit View history Tools Tools move to sidebar hide Actions Read Edit View history General What links here Related changes Upload file Permanent link Page information Cite this page Get shortened URL Print/export Download as PDF Printable version In other projects Wikimedia Commons Wikiquote Wikidata item Appearance move to sidebar hide From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia Video game character This article is about the video game character. For other uses, see Princess Daisy (disambiguation) . Fictional character Princess Daisy Mario character Promotional art by Shigehisa Nakaue (2021) First game Super Mario Land (1989) Voiced by Deanna Mustard (2003–2022) Giselle Fernandez (2023–present) Others Melissa Beckford ( Super Mario Compact Disco ) Kate Fleming ( Mario Tennis ) [ 1 ] Jen Taylor (2000–2003) Noriko Hidaka (Japanese DVD dub of Super Mario Bros film) Maya Okamoto (Japanese Nippon TV dub of Super Mario Bros film) Portrayed by Samantha Mathis (film) In-universe information Nationality Sarasaland Princess Daisy ( Japanese : デイジー姫 , Hepburn : Deijī-hime ) is a character in the Mario franchise. She debuted in the 1989 Game Boy launch game Super Mario Land as the ruler of Sarasaland where she was given the role of damsel in distress for Mario to rescue. The game’s official Japanese manual described the character as \"a slightly tomboyish and energetic princess\", a personality that would be defined through vocal performances and unique animations in later titles. [ 2 ] Since her appearance in Mario Tennis , she has been a staple playable character in Mario spin-off games, including Mario Party and Mario Kart . She also appears as a playable character in Super Smash Bros. Ultimate . Daisy has been primarily voiced by American voice actress Deanna Mustard from 2003 to 2022, who was succeeded by Giselle Fernandez starting with Super Mario Bros. Wonder . She is portrayed by Samantha Mathis in the live-action Super Mario Bros. film. Princess Daisy has been a popular character for her noticeable contrast to Peach and her memorable characterization in games such as the Mario Strikers series. Though the character had largely been exclusive to spin-off titles since 2000, she was later integrated into the mainline Super Mario series of video games as a playable character in Super Mario Run and Super Mario Bros. Wonder . Concept and creation [ edit ] Princess Daisy was created as a damsel in distress for Mario to rescue in Super Mario Land . [ 3 ] It was produced as a launch title for the Game Boy handheld game console by Gunpei Yokoi in partnership with Satoru Okada without the input of Shigeru Miyamoto . With the aim to create a scaled-down game based on the gameplay of the 1985 Super Mario Bros. , it moved away from the usual setting of the Mushroom Kingdom. [ 4 ] The development team created Sarasaland, named after a type of floral design, and made Daisy to match that concept. [ 5 ] Daisy's flower emblem is used to represent her in many games. Daisy was added to Mario Tennis for the Nintendo 64 due to the developer Camelot Software Planning wanting someone whose body shape was appropriate for real-life sports. [ 6 ] D", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_2", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}], "stats": {"n_source_urls": 3, "n_image_urls": 1, "n_observations": 3}}
