{"id": "180", "question": "In 2024, a highly popular game was released in China. This game, generally categorized as a \"Souls-like,\" is based on Chinese mythology. Within the game, there is a tiger character proficient in forging weapons and armor, as well as in combat. The question is: what weapon does this character carry at its waist", "observations": [{"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Black Myth: Wukong - Wikipedia\nPAGE_TEXT: Black Myth: Wukong - Wikipedia Jump to content Main menu Main menu move to sidebar hide Navigation Main page Contents Current events Random article About Wikipedia Contact us Contribute Help Learn to edit Community portal Recent changes Upload file Special pages Search Search Appearance Donate Create account Log in Personal tools Donate Create account Log in Contents move to sidebar hide (Top) 1 Gameplay 2 Synopsis Toggle Synopsis subsection 2.1 Setting 2.2 Plot 3 Development 4 Release Toggle Release subsection 4.1 Post-release content 4.2 Media and merchandise 5 Reception Toggle Reception subsection 5.1 Reviews 5.2 Sales 5.3 Impact 5.4 Accolades 6 Notes 7 References 8 External links Toggle the table of contents Black Myth: Wukong 37 languages العربية مصرى Azərbaycanca Беларуская (тарашкевіца) Català 閩東語 / Mìng-dĕ̤ng-ngṳ̄ Čeština Deutsch Español فارسی Suomi Français 客家語 / Hak-kâ-ngî עברית Bahasa Indonesia Italiano 日本語 한국어 ລາວ Bahasa Melayu Nederlands Polski پښتو Português Русский Simple English Slovenčina ไทย Türkçe ئۇيغۇرچە / Uyghurche Українська Tiếng Việt 吴语 Vahcuengh 閩南語 / Bân-lâm-gí 粵語 中文 Edit links Article Talk English Read Edit View history Tools Tools move to sidebar hide Actions Read Edit View history General What links here Related changes Upload file Permanent link Page information Cite this page Get shortened URL Print/export Download as PDF Printable version In other projects Wikimedia Commons Wikiquote Wikidata item Appearance move to sidebar hide From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia 2024 video game 2024 video game Black Myth: Wukong Developer Game Science Publisher Game Science Director Feng Ji ‍ [ 1 ] Producer Feng Ji ‍ [ 2 ] Designer Jiang Baicun ‍ [ 2 ] Programmer Zhao Wenyong ‍ [ 2 ] Artist Yang Qi ‍ [ 1 ] [ 2 ] Engine Unreal Engine 5 Platforms PlayStation 5 Windows Xbox Series X/S Release PlayStation 5 , Windows August 20, 2024 Xbox Series X/S August 20, 2025 Genre Action role-playing Mode Single-player Black Myth: Wukong ‍ [ a ] is a 2024 action role-playing game developed and published by Game Science . The player assumes the role of the Destined One, a staff-wielding monkey, who embarks on a journey to recover six relics corresponding to Sun Wukong 's six senses. The game is inspired by the classical Chinese novel Journey to the West . It is the first installment in the Black Myth series. Black Myth: Wukong was released for PlayStation 5 and Windows on August 20, 2024, and for Xbox Series X/S on August 20, 2025. It received generally favorable reviews from critics and won several accolades including Game of the Year awards. It sold 20 million units in its first month, making it one of the fastest-selling games of all time. Black Myth: Zhong Kui is the next entry in the series. Gameplay [ edit ] Black Myth: Wukong is an action role-playing game . [ 4 ] [ 5 ] [ 6 ] [ 7 ] It has elements characteristic of the Soulslike subgenre. [ 6 ] [ 7 ] It is played in single-player mode ‍ [ 8 ] [ 9 ] [ 10 ] from a third-person perspective . [ 4 ] This gameplay demonstrates the Destined One performing a few of the possible moves corresponding to each of the staff stances. [ 11 ] It also shows dodges, a spell (Rock Solid), and a varied combo (Resolute Strike) countering incoming attacks. [ 12 ] The player controls the Destined One, a monkey protagonist based on Sun Wukong from the classical Chinese novel Journey to the West . [ 5 ] [ 8 ] The protagonist's weapon is a staff much like the Ruyi Jingu Bang from the novel. [ 5 ] [ 13 ] The staff can extend and shrink in size during combat. [ 5 ] Its moveset is versatile through the staff stances, which includes the smash, pillar, and thrust stance. [ 8 ] [ 14 ] [ 15 ] [ 16 ] [ 17 ] The combat mechanics involve resource management. [ 18 ] Focus is accumulated by landing light attacks, executing well-timed dodges, and other means. [ 19 ] [ 20 ] A focus point is gained when the meter for focus is filled up. [ 18 ] These points can be used to initiate heavy attacks. [ 20 ] A hea", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_0", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Yin Tiger - Black Myth: Wukong Guide - IGN\nPAGE_TEXT: Yin Tiger - Black Myth: Wukong Guide - IGN Focus Reset Skip to content Black Myth: Wukong Guide Start tracking progress Create a free account or Log in. Find in guide Task Search Checklists Interactive Maps Table of Contents Black Myth: Wukong Guide Essential Tips and Tricks Things Black Myth Wukong Doesn't Tell You Walkthrough Side Questlines Boss List and Guides Best Skills to Unlock Best Settings on PS5 and PC Secrets in Black Myth Wukong Secret Bosses in Black Myth Wukong Key Items How-to Guides Weapons Armor and Gear Curios Transformation Spells Vessels Gourds Drinks Soaks Consumable Items Crafting Materials Medicine Ingredients Collectibles Celestial Pill Locations Spirit Locations Best Spirits to Use Meditation Spots Achievements and Trophies Guide About IGN's Black Myth: Wukong Guide Writers Back To Top Black Myth: Wukong Guide Guide Checklists Maps Task Search Task Search Checklists Guides Markers Videos Sort and Filter No Results Checklists New Checklist All Lists My Checklists All Story Completion Bosses and Enemies Collectibles Weapons and Gear Transformations Equippable Consumables Locations Achievements and Trophies Story Completion Main Quests Bosses and Enemies Bosses Collectibles Key Items Weapons and Gear Weapons Weapons and Gear Armor and Unique Gear Weapons and Gear Vessels Transformations Transformation Spells Equippable Gourds Equippable Drinks Equippable Soaks Collectibles Spirits Collectibles Luojia Fragrant Vines Collectibles Awaken Wine Worms Collectibles Curios Consumables Celestial Pills Consumables Consumable Items Locations Meditation Spots Achievements and Trophies Achievements and Trophies All Lists My Checklists How creative can you get with your first free checklist? Create a free account All Interactive Maps and Locations Yin Tiger By Brendan Graeber , Echo Apsey , Lauren Harper , +13 more Updated : Sep 16, 2024 9:01pm UTC The Yin Tiger is a character merchant and optional boss battle in Black Myth Wukong. One of the Zodiac Deities that resdies in the Zodiac Village, you'll be able to challenge this fearsome blacksmith to a sparring match, and earn the right transform into him for short periods. Rewards: Ebon Flow Transformation Spell, Extra Curio Slot Where to Find Yin Tiger In order to reach the Yin Tiger, you must first unlock the Zodiac Village. This can be done in Chapter 3, after arriving at the North Shore of the Bitter Lake. By heading left along the shore, you'll meet Chen Loong, and will also need to defeat him in combat so that he'll calm down enough to ask you for aid. Get the medicine Chen Loong seeks from the Xu Dog back in Chapter 2 under the Tiger Temple, and you'll be given the Ruyi Scroll to teleport you to the Zodiac Village, a hub of merchants -- many of whom you've already met. One of these merchants is the Yin Tiger, who serves as a blacksmith to help upgrade your armor, and you can also choose to challenge him to a duel. Yin Tiger Boss Fight and Guide Be warned: challenging the Yin Tiger to a duel won't be an easy fight. In fact, even though you can challenge him early on in Chapter 3, it's highly recommend that you hold off on challenging him until you've reach the end of or completed New Thunderclap Temple, and gained additional upgrades, gear, and Spirits to challenge him with. The Yin Tiger is an absolutely ferocious enemy who holds nothing back, and can teleport at will to confuse and disorient you before unleashing incredibly destructive attacks. There is some good news to this fight: Since it's a \"friendly\" duel, you won't actually be killed, and instead will simply stop fighting once you lose all of your health -- which will be instantly replenished. The Yin Tiger also gives you a lengthy period at the start to use whatever consumables you have on hand to prepare before the fight truly begins. Once it does, you'll need to be on top of your game and quickly adapt to his different moves, teleports, and fake-out attacks. His most common attacks come from large two-", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_1", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Just a moment...\nPAGE_TEXT: Just a moment... Enable JavaScript and cookies to continue", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_2", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}], "stats": {"n_source_urls": 3, "n_image_urls": 0, "n_observations": 3}}
