{"id": "194", "question": "How many rubber pads are included in total for the A, B, X, Y, Guide (Xbox logo), Start, and Back buttons on the Xbox 360 wireless controller?", "observations": [{"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Xbox 360 Wireless Controller Bottom Panel Replacement - iFixit 维修指南\nPAGE_TEXT: Xbox 360 Wireless Controller Bottom Panel Replacement - iFixit 维修指南 跳转到主内容 修复你的物品 社区 商店 加入维修社区 - 创建账户 Xbox 360 Wireless Controller Bottom Panel Replacement 简介 Use this guide to replace the bottom panel of your controller that you cracked by throwing it at the TV. 你所需要的 步骤 1 Battery Depress the battery release button on the top of the controller. Remove the battery holder from the controller. The standard option for Xbox 360 Wireless Controllers Battery Packs is AA batteries. A rechargeable battery is also available, but both battery options are removed from the controller in the same way. 编辑 添加一条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 2 Rear Case 在这个步骤中使用的工具： Tweezers $4.99 购买 Use a pair of tweezers to peel the barcode sticker from the battery compartment. 编辑 添加一条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 3 Remove the seven 9.3 mm T8 Security Torx screws securing the rear case to the front case. 编辑 5条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 4 在这个步骤中使用的工具： Spudger $2.99 购买 Insert a Spudger between the front and rear cases along the left edge of the controller. Rotate the spudger toward the front of the controller, prying the two cases apart. 编辑 添加一条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 5 Insert a spudger between the front and rear cases, near the headphone jack. Rotate the spudger toward the front of the controller to pry the two cases apart. 编辑 添加一条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 6 Grasp the controller by the battery compartment and the headphone jack. Lift the battery compartment away from the headphone jack, separating the rear case from the front case and logic board. The battery contact springs are held in place by slots in the battery housing in the rear case. Be sure to realign them properly during reassembly. 编辑 2条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 7 Vibration Motors Use the flat end of a spudger to remove the vibration motor cable, moving it upward from its socket on the logic board. Lift the vibration motor out of the front case. 编辑 添加一条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 8 Remove the vibration motor from the other side of the controller using the same method previously described. The left motor has significantly more counterweight than the right motor. 编辑 2条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 9 Logic Board Lifting from the headphone jack and power plug, remove the logic board from the front case. 编辑 3条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 10 Bottom Panel Lift the bumper panel off of the front case. 编辑 添加一条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 11 Remove the rubber pad from the back of the D-pad. 编辑 添加一条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 12 Remove the two 7.0 mm silver Phillips screws from the back of the D-pad. 编辑 添加一条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 13 在这个步骤中使用的工具： Tweezers $4.99 购买 The D-pad is secured to its backing by two diagonal clips, shown in red. Use a pair of tweezers and squeeze the clips together to release the D-pad from its backing. 编辑 添加一条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 14 Lift the D-pad backing out of its compartment on the front case. The D-pad remains below the front case. The D-pad will fall once its backing is removed. Be sure to support it as you remove the backing. The backing is slotted to its compartment to ensure that it will always be aligned properly. 编辑 添加一条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 15 Remove the rubber pad from the back of the input buttons. 编辑 添加一条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 16 Using a pair or tweezers, remove the following buttons from the front panel: A Button B Button X Button Y Button Start Button Select Button Guide Button 编辑 添加一条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 17 Using a pair of tweezers, remove the LED ring from the front panel. 编辑 添加一条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 步骤 18 Insert a spudger between the lower panel and front case. Slide the spudger along the gap between the two case components. Lift the lower panel off of the front case. 编辑 添加一条评论 添加一条评论 添加评论 1024 取消 发帖评论 结论 To reassemble your device, follow these instructions in reverse order. 成功完成！给作者 + 30 分! 你已经完成了！ 取消：我没有完成这个指南。 20等其他人完成本指南。 作者 与 3其他贡献者 Brett Hartt 于04/12/10注册 131,847 声望 创作了144篇指南 徽", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_0", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}], "stats": {"n_source_urls": 1, "n_image_urls": 0, "n_observations": 1}}
