7 (8045), 453-460 , 2025 41 2025 Structural basis for Ca 2+ activation of the heteromeric PKD1L3/PKD2L1 channel Q Su, M Chen, Y Wang, B Li, D Jing, X Zhan, Y Yu, Y Shi Nature communications 12 (1), 4871 , 2021 29 2021 Cryo-EM structures of human TMEM120A and TMEM120B M Ke, Y Yu, C Zhao, S Lai, Q Su, W Yuan, L Yang, D Deng, K Wu, W Zeng, ... Cell discovery 7 (1), 77 , 2021 26 2021 Quantitatively relating gene expression to light intensity via the serial connection of blue light sensor and CRISPRi H Wu, Y Wang, Y Wang, X Cao, Y Wu, Z Meng, Q Su, Z Wang, S Yang, ... ACS synthetic biology 3 (12), 979-982 , 2014 14 2014 Molecular and structural basis of the dual regulation of the polycystin-2 ion channel by small-molecule ligands Z Wang, M Chen, Q Su, TDC Morais, Y Wang, E Nazginov, AR Pillai, ... Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences 121 (12), e2316230121 , 2024 8 2024 Author Correction: Cryo-EM structures of the full-length human KCC2 and KCC3 cation-chloride cotransporters X Chi, X Li, Y Chen, Y Zhang, Q Su, Q Zhou Cell Research 31 (8), 941 , 2021 3 2021 Phosphoantigen-Driven Dissociation of Butyrophilin Oligomers Activates γδ T Cells W Xin, B Huang, W Gao, W Zhang, Y Hu, Y Liu, E Liang, Y Shi, Q Su, ... bioRxiv, 2025.09. 26.677252 , 2025 1 2025 Molecular Mechanisms Underlying Human Vγ9Vδ2 T Cell Activation by Butyrophilin-3 (BTN3) Targeted Antibodies B Huang, W Xin, W Zhang, W Gao, Y Hu, Y Liu, Q Su, Q Zhou bioRxiv, 2025.10. 21.681109 , 2025 2025 BPS2025-Molecular and structural basis of the regulation of TRPP2 channel by small molecule ligands Z Wang, M Chen, Q Su, TDC Morais, Y Wang, F Qian, Y Shi, Y Yu Biophysical Journal 124 (3), 192a , 2025 2025 Cryo-EM structures of the full-length human KCC2 and KCC3 cation-chloride cotransporters (vol 31, pg 482, 2021) X Chi, X Li, Y Chen, Y Zhang, Q Su, Q Zhou CELL RESEARCH 31 (8), 941-941 , 2021 2021 系统目前无法执行此操作，请稍后再试。 文章 1–15 展开 隐私权 条款 帮助 关于学术搜索 Google 搜索帮助", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_7", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Structures of human γδ T cell receptor–CD3 complex | Nature\nPAGE_TEXT: Structures of human γδ T cell receptor–CD3 complex | Nature Skip to main content Thank you for visiting nature.com. You are using a browser version with limited support for CSS. To obtain the best experience, we recommend you use a more up to date browser (or turn off compatibility mode in Internet Explorer). In the meantime, to ensure continued support, we are displaying the site without styles and JavaScript. Advertisement View all journals Search My Account Login Content Explore content About the journal Publish with us Sign up for alerts RSS feed nature articles article Structures of human γδ T cell receptor–CD3 complex Download PDF Download PDF Article Open access Published: 24 April 2024 Structures of human γδ T cell receptor–CD3 complex Weizhi Xin ORCID: orcid.org/0009-0001-3214-9155 1 , 2 , 3 na1 , Bangdong Huang 1 , 2 , 3 na1 , Ximin Chi 1 , 2 , 3 na1 nAff4 , Yuehua Liu 1 , 2 , 3 , Mengjiao Xu 1 , 2 , 3 , Yuanyuan Zhang 1 , 2 , 3 , Xu Li ORCID: orcid.org/0000-0002-9401-6382 1 , 2 , 3 , Qiang Su ORCID: orcid.org/0000-0002-5852-4582 1 , 2 , 3 na1 & … Qiang Zhou ORCID: orcid.org/0000-0002-6237-8813 1 , 2 , 3 Show authors Nature volume 630 , pages 222–229 ( 2024 ) Cite this article 48k Accesses 55 Citations 74 Altmetric Metrics details Subjects Antigen presentation Cryoelectron microscopy Abstract Gamma delta (γδ) T cells, a unique T cell subgroup, are crucial in various immune responses and immunopathology 1 , 2 , 3 . The γδ T cell receptor (TCR), which is generated by γδ T cells, recognizes a diverse range of antigens independently of the major histocompatibility complex 2 . The γδ TCR associates with CD3 subunits, initiating T cell activation and holding great potential in immunotherapy 4 . Here we report the structures of two prototypical human Vγ9Vδ2 and Vγ5Vδ1 TCR–CD3 complexes 5 , 6 , revealing two distinct assembly mechanisms that depend on Vγ usage. The Vγ9Vδ2 TCR–CD3 complex is monomeric, with considerable conformational flexibility in the TCRγ–TCRδ extracellular domain and connecting peptides. The length of the connecting peptides regulates the ligand association and T cell activation. A cholesterol-like molecule wedges into the transmembrane region, exerting an inhibitory role in TCR signalling. The Vγ5Vδ1 TCR–CD3 complex displays a dimeric architecture, whereby two protomers nestle back to back through the Vγ5 domains of the TCR extracellular domains. Our biochemical and biophysical assays further corroborate the dimeric structure. Importantly, the dimeric form of the Vγ5Vδ1 TCR is essential for T cell activation. These findings reveal organizing principles of the γδ TCR–CD3 complex, providing insights into the unique properties of γδ TCR and facilitating immunotherapeutic interventions. Similar content being viewed by others Structural characterization of two γδ TCR/CD3 complexes Article Open access 02 January 2025 Structure of a fully assembled γδ T cell antigen receptor Article Open access 15 August 2024 γδ T-cell autoresponses to ectopic membrane proteins: a new type of pattern recognition Article Open access 13 February 2025 Main T cells are critical components of the vertebrate immune system, defending against invading pathogens and malignant cells. Human T lymphocytes are classified into two lineages, αβ and γδ T cells, based on their expression of either αβ or γδ T cell receptors (TCRs) 1 , 2 . In contrast to conventional αβ T cells, γδ T cells exhibit both adaptive and innate immune properties, constituting a unique lymphocyte population 3 , 7 . γδ T cells provide broad protective immune responses against various infectious and sterile stresses, including cytomegalovirus and Mycobacterium tuberculosis infections, tumour growth and tissue dysregulation 2 , 3 , 8 . The γδ TCR is a heterodimer comprising TCRγ and TCRδ chains, discovered in the mid 1980s 9 , 10 , 11 , 12 . Analogous to the αβ TCR, TCRγ and TCRδ chains undergo somatic recombination of variable (V), diversity (D) and joining (J) gene segme", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_8", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}], "stats": {"n_source_urls": 9, "n_image_urls": 0, "n_observations": 6}}
{"id": "234", "question": "There's an Apple phone with an external X71 baseband and a non-metal encapsulated battery. A YouTube blogger whose name includes 'WekiHome' published a teardown video of this phone in 2024. In that video, what was the  acoustic chamber projected size of this phone?", "observations": [{"text": "PAGE_TITLE: iPhone 16e's Gimped C1 5G Modem Battles Snapdragon X71 With Surprising Results | HotHardware\nPAGE_TEXT: iPhone 16e's Gimped C1 5G Modem Battles Snapdragon X71 With Surprising Results | HotHardware Skip to content ≡ Full View Mode PC COMPONENTS SYSTEMS MOBILE IT INFRASTRUCTURE LEISURE VIDEOS BLOGS SHOP SUBSCRIBE SWITCH TO DESKTOP SIGN OUT SHOP SEND US TIPS JOIN LOG IN Search all All News Features Blogs CATEGORIES Reviews News Blogs Shop PC COMPONENTS All PC Components Processors Graphics/Sound Motherboards Storage Misc SYSTEMS All Systems DIY Small Form Factor Desktops MOBILE All Mobile Laptops Smartphones Tablets Gadgets IT INFRASTRUCTURE All IT Infrastructure Workstation Data Center/Enterprise Cloud Software Security LEISURE All Leisure Entertainment Gaming Social And Internet VIDEOS All videos 2.5 Geeks Reviews/How Tos BLOGS Shop Subscribe TRENDING: Samsung Galaxy S26 Dell XPS 14 With Panther Lake Intel Panther Lake AMD Ryzen 7 9850X3D Dell UltraSharp U52 52-Inch Monitor home News iPhone 16e's Gimped C1 5G Modem Battles Snapdragon X71 With Surprising Results by Aaron Leong — Thursday, February 27, 2025, 10:35 AM EDT Comments The launch of Apple's iPhone 16e has been met with equal parts excitement and equal parts befuddlement. While the new phone sports many flagship features such as an A18 chipset, satellite connectivity, and larger battery, certain aspects (undoubtedly due to cost-cutting) have left some folks disappointed. One of the biggest spotlights has been cast on the 16e's C1 modem and its 5G performance. However, all might not be what they seem with Apple's first ever in-house built modem. Apple's modem, the C1 5G, has so far likely been unfairly criticized for lacking key features like mmWave support and for not being as tried-and-true as the Qualcomm modems used in prior iPhone models. Sure, it's Cupertino's first homemade attempt, but we believe that in the 16e the company was able to keep the MSRP reasonable by omitting mmWave (which is unpopular and unreliable anyway). Ultimately what matters is if real-world 5G performance can be close, if not better than some of its pricier stablemates. Strengthening the case for the C1 is a recent test by YouTuber Dave2D when he compared a C1-equipped iPhone 16e to a Qualcomm Snapdragon X71-equipped iPhone 16 Pro Max. Running some Ookla Speedtests, the reviewer saw the Pro Max topping out at about 153Mbps, while the 16e blasted through 200Mbps no problem. Other review outlets have mostly found that the C1 doesn't feel shortchanged, instead delivering consist and reliable 5G performance, although never trouncing higher-end iPhone 16s like Dave2D's test. One factor to consider about these findings, however, is that they were conducted primarily in well-developed areas or cities, meaning plenty of cell towers. For example, Dave2D's test was made in Toronto, Canada, which means both tested devices likely had stable 5G throughput. If the same test was made in an area with less reliable reception, it's possible that the Snapdragon modem might perform better. We're sure that more tests will soon appear to aide in this discussion. Say what you want to say, the C1 is an impressive first effort from Apple considering how the strong Speedtests results so far combined with no reports of connection stability issues and the like. Along with an 11% larger battery than the iPhone 16, the modem's power efficient design is claimed to significantly extend the iPhone 16e 's endurance. Comments Tags: modem , 5G , (NASDAQ:AAPL) , iphone 16e AL Aaron Leong Tech enthusiast, YouTuber, engineer, rock climber, family guy. 'Nuff said. Add as a preferred source on Google If link fails, search Google for HotHardware news , open Top Stories and click the star. TOP STORIES KEEP INFORMED Stay updated with the latest news and updates. Subscribe to our newsletter! Subscribe Now SITE Home Reviews News Blogs Full Site Sitemap CATEGORIES PC Components Systems Mobile IT Infrastructure Leisure Videos COMPANY About Advertise News Tips Contact Privacy Policy HotTech MORE Accessibility Shop STAY CONNECTED Twitter Face", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_0", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: ENG)iPhone 16 Pro 系列拆解：一年一度，但戏份不足～ 【享拆】- 微机分WekiHome - YouTube\nPAGE_TEXT: ENG)iPhone 16 Pro 系列拆解：一年一度，但戏份不足～ 【享拆】- 微机分WekiHome - YouTube About Press Copyright Contact us Creator Advertise Developers Terms Privacy Policy & Safety How YouTube works Test new features © 2026 Google LLC", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_1", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}], "stats": {"n_source_urls": 2, "n_image_urls": 0, "n_observations": 2}}
