{"id": "1004", "question": "The image shows a specialty food from a city in China. The city hosted a winter swimming competition in January 2024. At the opening ceremony, when the referee representative took the oath, what color was the lanyard for their badge?", "observations": [{"text": "PAGE_TITLE: 央视来打卡的美食，就藏在敦化这座宝藏小城里_澎湃号·政务_澎湃新闻-The Paper\nPAGE_TEXT: 央视来打卡的美食，就藏在敦化这座宝藏小城里_澎湃号·政务_澎湃新闻-The Paper 下载客户端 登录 无障碍 +1 央视来打卡的美食，就藏在敦化这座宝藏小城里 2024-06-18 14:25 来源： 澎湃新闻·澎湃号·政务 字号 不知道各位小伙伴 有没有注意到？ 吉林美食再次登上央视！ 而这次央视聚焦的 则是延边州敦化市 CCTV-17农业农村频道《谁知盘中餐》栏目 走进敦化市中成民俗餐厅 寻味纳豆明太鱼汤、纳豆烧豆角等 当地特色美食 这不禁让吉吉 想把敦化这个宝藏小城 分享给大家 “县”在就出发 第5期 就跟吉吉来到敦化 看看除了品尝央视推荐的特色美食 在敦化市还能干点啥吧！ - 纳豆明太鱼汤 - 在这里，明太鱼是家家户户都非常爱吃的美食。它的做法有很多种，纳豆明太鱼汤就是其中非常受当地居民喜爱的一种。煮好的明太鱼汤颜色奶白，再加上纳豆、黄豆芽、豆腐、萝卜等，清新爽口，营养丰富。 - 纳豆烧豆角 - 纳豆烧豆角也是一道好吃的美食。新鲜的东北豆角有嚼头、耐大火，下锅炸到金黄松软，再加入过油的纳豆和干辣椒大火翻炒，豆角的香味被完全激发出来，再配上纳豆的鲜，好吃又爽口！ - 自制水豆腐 - 这里有一种朝鲜族人民特有的制作豆腐的方法，那就是水豆腐。在豆腐成型之前，加入豆浆并轻轻搅拌，然后静止15分钟，好吃的水豆腐就做好了。水豆腐比豆腐脑还滑嫩，你可以把它熬成豆腐汤，也可以把水豆腐直接拌在米饭里，再加上自己喜欢的酱料，一口下去，十分满足~ - 石板豆腐 - 除了水豆腐，这里还有很多种关于豆腐的做法，石板豆腐也是一道必尝的豆腐美食。酱料的香配上外酥里嫩的豆腐，一口咬下去，口感层次丰富，唇齿留香。 - 中成朝鲜族文旅小镇 - 中成朝鲜族文旅小镇就坐落在国家5A级景区六鼎山文化旅游区旁、东牟山下，依山傍水、风景优美、交通便利，这次上榜央视的美食就来自于该文旅小镇的中成民俗餐厅。 该村以朝鲜族“十长生”元素IP和朝鲜族市井文化为内容，打造集空间游玩、市井体验为一体的沉浸式生态村。走入这里，房屋白墙黑瓦，充满着古朴典雅的气息，漫步在小镇的街头巷尾，能感受到浓浓的民族风情。在这里，你还能欣赏到朝鲜族风情的歌舞，和当地的舞蹈演员一起载歌载舞，感受朝鲜族文化的魅力。 这里还会不定时举办朝鲜族的特色活动，如中国朝鲜族婚礼典礼仪式、婚礼花轿巡街活动、婚俗宴、飞天凤凰表演等，可以近距离感受朝鲜族文化。 这里的古老院落、特色餐厅、乡村会客厅、星空木屋区、生态农业采摘园等，无不吸引着众多游客前来打卡体验，感受小镇的独特魅力。 小贴士 地址： 中成朝鲜族生态村 吉林省延边朝鲜族自治州敦化市G201与山城街交叉口西南方向1899米 - 六鼎山文化旅游区 - 六鼎山文化旅游区内文化和生态相映成景，形成了具有独特魅力的复合型景观。这里如诗如画，是个宜居宜游、休闲养生的好地方。 走进六鼎山文化旅游区，你可以先来到正觉寺内，寺内绿树红墙，暮鼓晨钟，是祈福纳祥的好去处。 这里还建立了我国著名作家、编剧张笑天的文学馆。文学馆共两层，一层主要是文品学作展区，二层是影视作品展区，还有多功能报告厅、藏书室、文学创作室等。爱好文学创作的朋友，这里定会给你带来创作灵感和人生启迪！ 除了逛逛这些充满文化气息的景点，当你走到外面，你会发现这里的风景也是非常令人着迷。漫步在六鼎山环湖路上，湖面上清风徐来，波光粼粼，山林间树影斑驳，绿意盎然，让人心旷神怡，在这里能尽情享受到山水相映的绝美妙境与举目远眺的怡然风光。 如果喜欢热闹就来童趣氛围满分的六鼎山亲子游乐园，各种无动力游乐项目应有尽有，无论是大人还是小孩都能在这里畅玩一整天；如果想度过一段宁静悠闲的时光，那就约三五好友去六鼎山星空露营地，感受惬意好时光；逛了一天，如果感到疲惫，还能去泡一泡六鼎山温泉~ 小贴士 地址： 六鼎山文化旅游区 吉林省延边朝鲜族自治州敦化市江南镇 票价： 成人组合票 110元/人 学生/老人/儿童组合票 60元/人 开放时间： 8:00—16:30 电话： 0433—6688330 0433—6686120 - 雁鸣湖镇小山村 - 雁鸣湖镇小山村地处雁鸣湖国家级保护湿地腹地，背靠大山，三面环水，沿湖山林郁郁葱葱，湖面清澈如镜，自然景观秀丽。 你可以约上三五好友，来到雁鸣湖渔港，或坐上电瓶船，感受速度与激情；或乘上画舫船，感受泛舟湖上的诗意。 这里的民宿临水而建，一栋栋木屋整齐排列在水边，一推开窗户就能看见美丽的湖边景色。还能品尝到当地的特色美食，比如极具东北特色的铁锅炖以及鲜美的湖鱼等。 雁鸣湖湿地山水灵秀，有非常多的珍稀水鸟在此栖息，是国家级自然保护区。这里风光无限、草绿水清，波光粼粼的湖面上时不时有水鸟飞过，构成一幅绝美的生态画卷。 小贴士 地址： 小山村 吉林省延边朝鲜族自治州敦化市雁鸣湖镇 - 樱桃采摘园 - 不知不觉又来到了樱桃成熟的季节，敦化市樱桃采摘园位于江南镇站北村，距市区5公里，这里樱桃又大又甜，红彤彤的果实挂满枝头，一进去就能感受到樱桃散发出的浓郁果香。 来樱桃采摘园不仅能体验到亲自采摘的乐趣，还能丰富见识，贴近大自然，同时樱桃的新鲜度也绝对有保障。樱桃的采摘季节通常在4月至6月，采摘时颜色红中泛紫的樱桃会更甜哦~ 小贴士 地址： 站北村 吉林省延边朝鲜族自治州敦化市渤海街道 敦化四季分明 景色各异 这里有清澈的湖水 有浓烈醉人的绿意 还有源远流长的文化 这个夏天就来这里 尽情感受文化和绝美风光的碰撞吧~ 如需转载本文请注明来源悠游吉林 特别声明 本文为澎湃号作者或机构在澎湃新闻上传并发布，仅代表该作者或机构观点，不代表澎湃新闻的观点或立场，澎湃新闻仅提供信息发布平台。申请澎湃号请用电脑访问http://renzheng.thepaper.cn。 +1 收藏 我要举报 # 吉林 查看更多 查看更多 开始答题 查看更多 扫码下载 澎湃新闻客户端 Android版 iPhone版 iPad版 关于澎湃 加入澎湃 联系我们 广告合作 法律声明 隐私政策 澎湃矩阵 澎湃新闻微博 澎湃新闻公众号 澎湃新闻抖音号 派生万物开放平台 IP SHANGHAI SIXTH TONE 新闻报料 报料热线: 021-962866 报料邮箱: news@thepaper.cn 沪ICP备14003370号 沪公网安备31010602000299号 互联网新闻信息服务许可证：31120170006 增值电信业务经营许可证：沪B2-2017116 © 2014- 2026 上海东方报业有限公司 反馈", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_0", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: 敦化第七届国际冬泳邀请赛在敦化市渤海湖盛大开幕_比赛_延边_吉林\nPAGE_TEXT: 敦化第七届国际冬泳邀请赛在敦化市渤海湖盛大开幕_比赛_延边_吉林 新闻 体育 汽车 房产 旅游 教育 时尚 科技 财经 娱乐 敦化第七届国际冬泳邀请赛在敦化市渤海湖盛大开幕 2024-01-11 15:29 来源: 诗逸生活 发布于： 吉林省 1月11日，全国冬泳日系列活动，健康吉林 乐动冰雪，吉林省“一市一品”体育精品赛事活动，2023-2024延边冰雪旅游节之2024年吉林省大众冬泳挑战赛暨敦化第七届国际冬泳邀请赛在敦化市渤海湖盛大开幕，吉林省体育局二级巡视员孟刚宣布比赛开幕，延边州人大常委会副主任、敦化市委书记刘岩智为比赛鸣枪发令，延边州政府副秘书长崔东辉，吉林省体育局群体处处长张晓东，延边州体育局局长金国范，吉林省体育局体育产业发展指导中心副主任王庆芝，延边州体育局副局长金虎峰，敦化市文化广播电视和旅游局（体育局）局长高玲出席开幕仪式。敦化市委副书记、市长唐振生致开幕辞，副市长金冠主持开幕仪式。王丹丹、丁帆分别代表运动员、裁判员宣誓。 本次赛事由吉林省体育局、延边朝鲜族自治州人民政府主办，延边州体育局、敦化市人民政府承办，吉林省体育局体育产业发展指导中心、吉林省体育场馆协会、延边体育彩票管理中心、敦化市文化广播电视和旅游局（体育局）协办。共有来自香港、俄罗斯、比利时、德国、英国、泰国、缅甸、印度尼西亚等35个国家和地区的65支代表队700名运动员参赛，年纪最小的9岁，最大的78岁高龄。开幕式活动现场参与人数达10000余人。 展开全文 比赛现场，世界各地参赛选手冒着严寒顽强拼搏、迎难而上、全力冲刺。经过紧张激烈的角逐，充分发挥了超越自我、团结一致的体育精神。 获得29岁以下男子组第一名的是鲁斯古拉科夫普拉东，第二名伊利亚·安德里亚诺维奇，第三名罗斯波加季诺夫·伊万；获得29岁以下女子组第一名的是古兹涅曹娃·瓦龙妮娜，第二名鲁斯科茹科娃·克里斯蒂娜，第三名杜宇涵。 今年78岁的高文亮，接触冬泳已经40余年，此次是专程从北京来到敦化参赛。比赛结束后，准备去六鼎山、老白山、中成村等景点逛逛，品尝一下当地特色美食，回到北京，会介绍更多的亲朋好友来敦化旅游。 来源：敦化市文化广播电视和旅游局 返回搜狐，查看更多 平台声明：该文观点仅代表作者本人，搜狐号系信息发布平台，搜狐仅提供信息存储空间服务。 阅读 ( )", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_1", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}], "stats": {"n_source_urls": 2, "n_image_urls": 1, "n_observations": 2}}
{"id": "1006", "question": "This figure is from a paper published on arXiv. One of its authors has the initials SO. This author also submitted another paper on arXiv, with a submission date of November 9, 2020, and a final revision date of September 12, 2022. In Figure 5 of that other paper, which is on page 11 of the PDF version and page 10 of the main text, what color represents the solid line in the left plot?", "observations": [{"text": "PAGE_TITLE: Novel bounds on neutrino portal dark matter from leptonic meson decays\nPAGE_TEXT: Novel bounds on neutrino portal dark matter from leptonic meson decays 1 Introduction 2 Setup 3 Corrections to leptonic meson decays 3.1 Three-body decay M → ℓ ​ ψ ¯ ​ H M\\to\\ell\\,\\overline{\\psi}\\,H 3.2 One-loop correction to M → ℓ ​ ν ¯ ℓ M\\to\\ell\\,\\overline{\\nu}_{\\ell} 4 Analysis 4.1 Electron flavor 4.2 Muon flavor 5 Other constraints 6 Summary a a institutetext: Asia Pacific Center for Theoretical Physics, Pohang, 37673, Korea b b institutetext: Department of Physics, Pohang University of Science and Technology, Pohang, 37673, Korea c c institutetext: Department of Physics, Kyushu University, 744 Motooka, Nishi-ku, Fukuoka, 819-0395, Japan d d institutetext: Department of Physics, Kindai University, Higashi-Osaka, Osaka 577-8502, Japan Novel bounds on neutrino portal dark matter from leptonic meson decays Shohei Okawa d Yuji Omura shohei.okawa@apctp.org yomura@phys.kindai.ac.jp Abstract We investigate the potential of leptonic meson decays M → ℓ ​ ν ¯ ℓ M\\to\\ell\\bar{\\nu}_{\\ell} , where M M is a pseudo-scalar meson, as a probe of neutrino portal dark matter. The model of our focus features a neutral fermion ψ \\psi and scalar ϕ \\phi , which are coupled predominantly to neutrinos in the form ℒ ⊃ λ ​ ν ¯ L ​ ϕ ​ ψ R {\\cal L}\\supset\\lambda\\,\\overline{\\nu}_{L}\\,\\phi\\,\\psi_{R} . This interaction generates two corrections to the M → ℓ ​ ν ¯ ℓ M\\to\\ell\\bar{\\nu}_{\\ell} observables. The first one is a novel three-body decay process M → ℓ ​ ψ ¯ ​ ϕ M\\to\\ell\\bar{\\psi}\\phi . This process is enabled by the splitting of the off-shell anti-neutrino ν ¯ ℓ \\bar{\\nu}_{\\ell} into ψ \\psi and ϕ \\phi in the M → ℓ ​ ν ¯ ℓ M\\to\\ell\\bar{\\nu}_{\\ell} diagram. The helicity suppression in M → ℓ ​ ν ¯ ℓ M\\to\\ell\\bar{\\nu}_{\\ell} is absent in the three-body process, thereby forming a potentially large contribution to real experimental results, provided ψ \\psi and ϕ \\phi are invisible. The second one is one-loop radiative corrections to the weak vertex W ​ ℓ ​ ν ¯ ℓ W\\ell\\bar{\\nu}_{\\ell} , which do not modify the charged lepton spectrum but lead to enhancement or suppression of the partial M → ℓ ​ ν ¯ ℓ M\\to\\ell\\bar{\\nu}_{\\ell} decay width. To demonstrate the ability of the leptonic meson decays to probe the neutrino portal dark matter, we compute two corrections analytically and compare the modified meson branching ratios with the experimental data on the lepton flavor universality of pion and Kaon decays. The resulting constraints turn out to surpass the existing bounds in a large part of parameter spaces. † † preprint: KYUSHU-HET-342 1 Introduction Despite the tremendous success of the Standard Model (SM), many theoretical mysteries and empirical deficiencies remain unsolved in particle physics. Dark matter (DM), in particular, represents a compelling signal for physics beyond the SM (BSM) and has been actively investigated. For a long time, the primary attention has been paid to neutral stable particles, with electroweak (EW) scale masses and weakly interacting to SM particles, also known as Weakly Interacting Massive Particles (WIMPs) Lee:1977ua ; Hut:1977zn ; Sato:1977ye ; Vysotsky:1977pe ; Bernstein:1985th . The WIMP DM candidates not only are predicted in new physics models addressing the so-called hierarchy problem, but also can be naturally created from the SM plasma in the thermal history of the universe. Moreover, the very same interactions responsible for the thermal production can serve as a useful probe to directly test the WIMP DM scenario in terrestrial experiments. In the last decades, direct detection experiments have considerably improved the sensitivity to DM-nucleon scattering cross sections, albeit without any affirmative signals so far. These results provide very stringent constraints on a variety of WIMP DM models. Given the strong constraints on the traditional WIMP DM scenario, significant attention has recently been directed toward a light DM particle with a mass much below the EW scale. In this mass region, typically below the Ge", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_0", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: [2511.08102] Novel bounds on neutrino portal dark matter from leptonic meson decays\nPAGE_TEXT: [2511.08102] Novel bounds on neutrino portal dark matter from leptonic meson decays Skip to main content Learn about arXiv becoming an independent nonprofit. We gratefully acknowledge support from the Simons Foundation, member institutions , and all contributors. Donate > hep-ph > arXiv:2511.08102 Help | Advanced Search All fields Title Author Abstract Comments Journal reference ACM classification MSC classification Report number arXiv identifier DOI ORCID arXiv author ID Help pages Full text Search open search GO open navigation menu quick links Login Help Pages About --> High Energy Physics - Phenomenology arXiv:2511.08102 (hep-ph) [Submitted on 11 Nov 2025] Title: Novel bounds on neutrino portal dark matter from leptonic meson decays Authors: Shohei Okawa , Yuji Omura View a PDF of the paper titled Novel bounds on neutrino portal dark matter from leptonic meson decays, by Shohei Okawa and 1 other authors View PDF HTML (experimental) Abstract: We investigate the potential of leptonic meson decays $M \\to \\ell \\bar\\nu_\\ell$, where $M$ is a pseudo-scalar meson, as a probe of neutrino portal dark matter. The model of our focus features a neutral fermion $\\psi$ and scalar $\\phi$, which are coupled predominantly to neutrinos in the form ${\\cal L} \\supset \\lambda\\,\\overline\\nu_L\\,\\phi\\,\\psi_R$. This interaction generates two corrections to the $M \\to \\ell \\bar\\nu_\\ell$ observables. The first one is a novel three-body decay process $M \\to \\ell \\bar\\psi\\phi$. This process is enabled by the splitting of the off-shell anti-neutrino $\\bar\\nu_\\ell$ into $\\psi$ and $\\phi$ in the $M \\to \\ell \\bar\\nu_\\ell$ diagram. The helicity suppression in $M \\to \\ell \\bar\\nu_\\ell$ is absent in the three-body process, thereby forming a potentially large contribution to real experimental results, provided $\\psi$ and $\\phi$ are invisible. The second one is one-loop radiative corrections to the weak vertex $W\\ell \\bar\\nu_\\ell$, which do not modify the charged lepton spectrum but lead to enhancement or suppression of the partial $M \\to \\ell \\bar\\nu_\\ell$ decay width. To demonstrate the ability of the leptonic meson decays to probe the neutrino portal dark matter, we compute two corrections analytically and compare the modified meson branching ratios with the experimental data on the lepton flavor universality of pion and Kaon decays. The resulting constraints turn out to surpass the existing bounds in a large part of parameter spaces. Comments: 15 pages + references, 4 figures Subjects: High Energy Physics - Phenomenology (hep-ph) ; High Energy Physics - Experiment (hep-ex) Report number: KYUSHU-HET-342 Cite as: arXiv:2511.08102 [hep-ph] (or arXiv:2511.08102v1 [hep-ph] for this version) https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2511.08102 Focus to learn more arXiv-issued DOI via DataCite Submission history From: Shohei Okawa [ view email ] [v1] Tue, 11 Nov 2025 11:00:29 UTC (553 KB) Full-text links: Access Paper: View a PDF of the paper titled Novel bounds on neutrino portal dark matter from leptonic meson decays, by Shohei Okawa and 1 other authors View PDF HTML (experimental) TeX Source view license Current browse context: hep-ph < prev | next > new | recent | 2025-11 Change to browse by: hep-ex References & Citations INSPIRE HEP NASA ADS Google Scholar Semantic Scholar export BibTeX citation Loading... BibTeX formatted citation × loading... Data provided by: Bookmark Bibliographic Tools Bibliographic and Citation Tools Bibliographic Explorer Toggle Bibliographic Explorer ( What is the Explorer? ) Connected Papers Toggle Connected Papers ( What is Connected Papers? ) Litmaps Toggle Litmaps ( What is Litmaps? ) scite.ai Toggle scite Smart Citations ( What are Smart Citations? ) Code, Data, Media Code, Data and Media Associated with this Article alphaXiv Toggle alphaXiv ( What is alphaXiv? ) Links to Code Toggle CatalyzeX Code Finder for Papers ( What is CatalyzeX? ) DagsHub Toggle DagsHub ( What is DagsHub? ) GotitPub Toggle Gotit.pub ( What is GotitPub? ) Huggingface", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_1", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: [2011.04788] Light mass window of lepton portal dark matter\nPAGE_TEXT: [2011.04788] Light mass window of lepton portal dark matter Skip to main content Learn about arXiv becoming an independent nonprofit. We gratefully acknowledge support from the Simons Foundation, member institutions , and all contributors. Donate > hep-ph > arXiv:2011.04788 Help | Advanced Search All fields Title Author Abstract Comments Journal reference ACM classification MSC classification Report number arXiv identifier DOI ORCID arXiv author ID Help pages Full text Search open search GO open navigation menu quick links Login Help Pages About --> High Energy Physics - Phenomenology arXiv:2011.04788 (hep-ph) [Submitted on 9 Nov 2020 ( v1 ), last revised 12 Sep 2022 (this version, v5)] Title: Light mass window of lepton portal dark matter Authors: Shohei Okawa , Yuji Omura View a PDF of the paper titled Light mass window of lepton portal dark matter, by Shohei Okawa and 1 other authors View PDF Abstract: We explore a novel possibility that dark matter has a light mass below 1GeV in a lepton portal dark matter model. There are Yukawa couplings involving dark matter, left-handed leptons and an extra scalar doublet in the model. In the light mass region, dark matter is thermally produced via its annihilation into neutrinos. In order to obtain the correct relic abundance and avoid collider bounds, a neutral scalar is required to be light while charged scalars need to be heavier than the electroweak scale. Such a mass spectrum is realized by adjusting quartic couplings in the scalar potential or introducing an extra singlet scalar. It turns out that the mass region of 10MeV-10GeV is almost free from experimental and observational constraints. We also point out that searches for extra neutrino flux from galactic dark matter annihilations with neutrino telescopes are the best way to test our model. Comments: 26 pages, 10 figures; v4: version published in JHEP; v5: corrected an error in the Higgs decay width into 2gamma and figure 5 accordingly, main conclusion unchanged Subjects: High Energy Physics - Phenomenology (hep-ph) ; High Energy Astrophysical Phenomena (astro-ph.HE); High Energy Physics - Experiment (hep-ex) Cite as: arXiv:2011.04788 [hep-ph] (or arXiv:2011.04788v5 [hep-ph] for this version) https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2011.04788 Focus to learn more arXiv-issued DOI via DataCite Related DOI : https://doi.org/10.1007/JHEP02%282021%29231 Focus to learn more DOI(s) linking to related resources Submission history From: Shohei Okawa [ view email ] [v1] Mon, 9 Nov 2020 21:45:14 UTC (1,055 KB) [v2] Wed, 18 Nov 2020 02:21:27 UTC (1,055 KB) [v3] Mon, 25 Jan 2021 19:59:23 UTC (1,080 KB) [v4] Tue, 23 Feb 2021 21:01:56 UTC (1,080 KB) [v5] Mon, 12 Sep 2022 13:29:04 UTC (1,079 KB) Full-text links: Access Paper: View a PDF of the paper titled Light mass window of lepton portal dark matter, by Shohei Okawa and 1 other authors View PDF TeX Source view license Current browse context: hep-ph