{"id": "207", "question": "On a 1995 Toyota Camry Wagon LE (2.2L 5S-FE automatic transmission) vehicle, what is the resistance in ohms of the R840 resistor on the circuit board of the module responsible for determining ignition timing?", "observations": [{"text": "PAGE_TITLE: ECU Repair/Replacement? | Toyota Forum\nPAGE_TEXT: ECU Repair/Replacement? | Toyota Forum in this thread in this sub-forum in the entire site Advanced Search Cancel Create thread New Garage Forums More Login / Join What's New Forum Listing Marketplace Garage Answers Showcase Gallery Advanced Search Members FAQ Get the Fora App Dark Mode Light Mode Menu Log in Sign up Home Forums Toyota Passenger and Sports Car Forums Camry and Solara Forum Camry 3rd and 4th Gen '92-'01, Solara '99-'03 Podcast: Should You Buy a Used EV? JavaScript is disabled. For a better experience, please enable JavaScript in your browser before proceeding. Stillrunning S I been diagnosing engine stall/no start for several days. Engine starts and runs perfect when cold, after about 15-20 minutes of run time the engine stalls and will not restart until after cooling for about 20-30 minutes where it will run for another 15-20 minutes then stall again. It is a no spark problem. The 5 volt signal voltage that is fired from the ECU driver to switch the igniter chip to turn the 12 volt coil supply off and on is not happening. The 12 volt primary is always on. I have checked or substituted all the ignition components except the ECU which I will inspect today. So I'm asking where is the best place to get the ECU checked/repaired/replaced? I'm not trusting FleaBay but looking for a reputable shop. Thanks. ECU Repair/Replacement? Jump to Latest 17K views 27 replies 9 participants last post by Strega315 Dec 22, 2022 S Stillrunning Discussion starter 5,730 posts · Joined 2006 #1 · Feb 10, 2022 I been diagnosing engine stall/no start for several days. Engine starts and runs perfect when cold, after about 15-20 minutes of run time the engine stalls and will not restart until after cooling for about 20-30 minutes where it will run for another 15-20 minutes then stall again. It is a no spark problem. The 5 volt signal voltage that is fired from the ECU driver to switch the igniter chip to turn the 12 volt coil supply off and on is not happening. The 12 volt primary is always on. I have checked or substituted all the ignition components except the ECU which I will inspect today. So I'm asking where is the best place to get the ECU checked/repaired/replaced? I'm not trusting FleaBay but looking for a reputable shop. Thanks. 1995 Camry Wagon LE. 2.2 5S-FE, Auto, 261K Save Share Reply Quote Like Sort by Oldest first Oldest first Newest first Most reactions norm356 4,997 posts · Joined 2018 #2 · Feb 10, 2022 (Edited) Before throwing any more parts at it, I recommend to get the code(s) read. A '95 ought to have OBDII, which any local auto parts store should be able to read for you, for free. Then, tell us what that code is and we can better help you out. Reactions: zzyzzx Save Share Reply Quote Like norm356 4,997 posts · Joined 2018 #3 · Feb 10, 2022 If after reading the codes, if it turns out that your ECU is the culprit, then here's a site that others here have recommended / used for repair (mainly replacing all of the caps): ECM, ECU repair service for Mitsubishi, Honda, Geo & Suzuki $195., including return shipping - 5 year warranty But, usually it is enough to simply buy a used one from a salvage yard. Just make sure the part number is an exact match. Reactions: Elle_Rav4 Save Share Reply Quote Like S Stillrunning Discussion starter 5,730 posts · Joined 2006 #4 · Feb 10, 2022 I have done the code read. It's an OBDI so codes are read with CEL flashes. The CEL does not light when this occurs. There are two stored codes that I've had off and on for a while, IGF and IGT, but I don't think they're related. These codes have been off for a long time now. I've opened the ECU and nothing obvious. There is a place here in Raleigh with lifetime warranty. Car & Truck Engine Computers for Sale | Car Computer Exchange Going to call to see if they can inspect, test, repair if necessary. Their exchange units are $200. 1995 Camry Wagon LE. 2.2 5S-FE, Auto, 261K Save Share Reply Quote Like Strega315 3,045 posts · Joined 2020 #6 · Feb 10, 2022", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_0", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TEXT: ����\u0000\u0010JFIF\u0000\u0001\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0000��\u0002 ICC_PROFILE\u0000\u0001\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0002 lcms\u0002\u0010\u0000\u0000mntrRGB XYZ \u0007�\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0019\u0000\u0003\u0000)\u00009acspAPPL\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000��\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000�-lcms\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000 desc\u0000\u0000\u0000�\u0000\u0000\u0000^cprt\u0000\u0000\u0001\\\u0000\u0000\u0000 wtpt\u0000\u0000\u0001h\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0014bkpt\u0000\u0000\u0001|\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0014rXYZ\u0000\u0000\u0001�\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0014gXYZ\u0000\u0000\u0001�\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0014bXYZ\u0000\u0000\u0001�\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0014rTRC\u0000\u0000\u0001�\u0000\u0000\u0000@gTRC\u0000\u0000\u0001�\u0000\u0000\u0000@bTRC\u0000\u0000\u0001�\u0000\u0000\u0000@desc\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0003c2\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0