朱 学正 剧务 魏子鸿 场记 胡 善团苏大八裂带怕 涛、黄靖尧 布景师 秦枫 发行 刘霜叶、邓斯琪（总发行人）、 王丹（发行人） 参考资料 [2] 折叠 编辑本段 角色介绍 评复济许证挥失 李善德 演员 雷佳音 上林 署监事。性格耿直忠厚 ，做事认真执着。 育买略集势也华切被子散 李善德是算科出身，精于园艺。他本想为女儿赎回老宅 ，却意外被推为“荔枝使”， 负责从岭南运送鲜荔枝至长安。面对这一几乎不可能 完成的任务，他历经千难万险， 深入岭南考察，与果 起距居价吃然慢田列望 农合作，反复试验保鲜方法，最终成功将荔枝 件市鸡县影轻 运回长安。后因不满官 场腐败辞官，携女归隐岭南。 郑平安 演员 岳云鹏 李善德的小舅子 。性格机敏圆滑，擅长 舞技。郑平安出身荥阳郑氏，父亲因不愿与右 相同流合污被害，他也沦为 陪酒侍郎。受左相指派，他假冒右相使者马归云 前往岭南，搜集何 有光与右相勾结的 证据。在岭南，他历经艰险 ，最终扳倒何有光。后为保护李善德及袖儿，与右相派来的杀手力战身亡。 云清 演员安沺 空浪坊坊 令创己那粒乙内比亚国 主。性格聪慧机敏，心思缜密。云清幼时家破人亡，后被卢奂救下并培养为 再 左相在岭南的暗探，以“空浪先生”的身份在岭南经 重端些聚密便肥适风坏 营书局，暗中搜集情报。她协助郑 平安完成任务，揭露何有光火 烧骑鲸楼、谋害海虎的罪行，更在关键时刻救下阿", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_1", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: 长安的荔枝 剧照\nPAGE_TEXT: 长安的荔枝 剧照 登录/注册 下载豆瓣客户端 豆瓣 6.0 全新发布 × 豆瓣 扫码直接下载 iPhone · Android 豆瓣 读书 电影 音乐 播客 同城 小组 阅读 FM 时间 豆品 豆瓣电影 搜索： 影讯&购票 选电影 选剧集 排行榜 影评 2025年度榜单 2025年度报告 长安的荔枝 的剧照 第270张/共319张 上一张 / 下一张 > 浏览所有剧照 查看大图 查看大图 推荐 2人 喜欢 喜欢 > 我来回应 后退 前进 图片信息 · · · · · · 剧集名称： 长安的荔枝 图片类型：截图 大图尺寸：1920x804 来自： 喜悦之地 上传于2025-06-08 > 去 长安的荔枝 的页面 投诉不良信息 © 2005－2026 douban.com, all rights reserved 北京豆网科技有限公司 关于豆瓣 · 在豆瓣工作 · 联系我们 · 法律声明 · 帮助中心 · 移动应用", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_2", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}], "stats": {"n_source_urls": 3, "n_image_urls": 1, "n_observations": 3}}
{"id": "1019", "question": "This image is from a paper published on arXiv. One of its authors has the initials PBD. He also submitted another paper on arXiv, with a version dated October 27, 2025. In FIG. 2 on page 5 of that other paper, which colored solid line in the plot on the right has the smallest y-axis value at the starting position?", "observations": [{"text": "PAGE_TITLE: NuFast-Earth: Efficient Atmospheric, Solar, and Supernova Neutrino Propagation Through the Earth\nPAGE_TEXT: NuFast-Earth: Efficient Atmospheric, Solar, and Supernova Neutrino Propagation Through the Earth I Introduction II Earth II.1 Earth Models II.2 Trajectories III The Algorithm III.1 One Layer Amplitude III.1.1 Calulation of Eigenvalues III.1.2 Calculation of Eigenvectors III.2 Amplitudes to Probabilities III.2.1 Combining the Layer Amplitudes III.2.2 Transforming back to the flavor basis IV Astrophysical Neutrinos from the Sun or a Supernova IV.1 Solar Neutrinos IV.2 Galactic Supernova Neutrinos V Results VI Code Usage VII Speed, Precision, and Recommendations VII.1 Speed VII.2 Precision VII.3 Recommendations VIII Conclusions A Validation B Determinant and Adjugate of ( λ ​ I − H ) (\\lambda I-H) : † † thanks: 0000-0002-5209-872X † † thanks: 0000-0003-2028-6782 NuFast-Earth : Efficient Atmospheric, Solar, and Supernova Neutrino Propagation Through the Earth Peter B. Denton pdenton@bnl.gov High Energy Theory Group, Physics Department Brookhaven National Laboratory, Upton, NY 11973, USA Stephen J. Parke parke@fnal.gov Theoretical Physics Department, Fermi National Accelerator Laboratory, Batavia, IL 60510, USA (November 6, 2025) Abstract Algorithms for computing neutrino oscillation probabilities in sharply varying matter potentials such as the Earth are becoming increasingly important. As the next generation of experiments, DUNE and HyperK as well as the IceCube upgrade and KM3NeT, come online, the computational cost for atmospheric and solar neutrinos will continue to increase. To address these issues, we expand upon our previous algorithm for long-baseline calculations to efficiently handle probabilities through the Earth for atmospheric, nighttime solar, and supernova neutrinos. The algorithm is fast, flexible, and accurate. It can handle arbitrary Earth models with two different schemes for varying density profiles. We also provide a c++ implementation of the code called NuFast-Earth along with a detailed user manual. The code intelligently keeps track of repeated calculations and only recalculates what is needed on each successive call which can also help provide significant speed-ups. † † preprint: FERMILAB-PUB-25-0704-T Contents I Introduction II Earth II.1 Earth Models II.2 Trajectories III The Algorithm III.1 One Layer Amplitude III.1.1 Calulation of Eigenvalues III.1.2 Calculation of Eigenvectors III.2 Amplitudes to Probabilities III.2.1 Combining the Layer Amplitudes III.2.2 Transforming back to the flavor basis IV Astrophysical Neutrinos from the Sun or a Supernova IV.1 Solar Neutrinos IV.2 Galactic Supernova Neutrinos V Results VI Code Usage VII Speed, Precision, and Recommendations VII.1 Speed VII.2 Precision VII.3 Recommendations VIII Conclusions A Validation B Determinant and Adjugate of ( λ ​ I − H ) (\\lambda I-H) : I Introduction The Wolfenstein matter effect [ 1 ] provides a key modification to neutrino oscillation probabilities in many of the environments where we observe neutrino oscillations. The matter effect can muddy the extraction of some fundamental oscillation parameters and yet is also essential in the extraction of others, see e.g. [ 2 ] . Nonetheless, other than solar neutrinos experiencing the effect inside the Sun, there has not yet been a clear detection of the matter effect in other environments, notably within the Earth. Current and next-generation experiments are aiming to make incredibly precise measurements of neutrino oscillations from a variety of sources. Atmospheric neutrinos will provide precision measurements of sin 2 ⁡ 2 ​ θ 23 \\sin^{2}2\\theta_{23} and Δ ​ m 32 2 \\Delta m^{2}_{32} as well as some information on the octant of θ 23 \\theta_{23} , θ 13 \\theta_{13} , the mass ordering, and δ \\delta [ 3 , 4 , 5 , 6 ] and solar neutrinos should provide [ 7 , 8 , 9 ] the first clear measurement of the day-night effect [ 10 , 11 , 12 , 13 ] which the current data is only beginning to hint at [ 14 ] . Extracting the most information possible from these measurements requires incredibly precise p", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_0", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: [2510.23713] Glimpsing Physics of Nano-Hz Gravitational Waves in Neutrinos from Core-Collapse Supernovae\nPAGE_TEXT: [2510.23713] Glimpsing Physics of Nano-Hz Gravitational Waves in Neutrinos from Core-Collapse Supernovae Skip to main content Learn about arXiv becoming an independent nonprofit. We gratefully acknowledge support from the Simons Foundation, member institutions , and all contributors. Donate > hep-ph > arXiv:2510.23713 Help | Advanced Search All fields Title Author Abstract Comments Journal reference ACM classification MSC classification Report number arXiv identifier DOI ORCID arXiv author ID Help pages Full text Search open search GO open navigation menu quick links Login Help Pages About --> High Energy Physics - Phenomenology arXiv:2510.23713 (hep-ph) [Submitted on 27 Oct 2025] Title: Glimpsing Physics of Nano-Hz Gravitational Waves in Neutrinos from Core-Collapse Supernovae Authors: Hooman Davoudiasl , Peter B. Denton , Anna M. Suliga View a PDF of the paper titled Glimpsing Physics of Nano-Hz Gravitational Waves in Neutrinos from Core-Collapse Supernovae, by Hooman Davoudiasl and 2 other authors View PDF HTML (experimental) Abstract: The growing evidence for nano-hertz gravitational waves, from NANOGrav and other observations, may be pointing to a cosmological first-order phase transition at temperatures of $\\mathcal{O}(10-100)\\;\\mathrm{MeV}$. Such an interpretation requires dynamics beyond the Standard Model in this energy range. If so, it may well be the case that core-collapse supernova explosions would recreate the first-order phase transition leaving a unique imprint on the spectrum of neutrinos emitted in the initial few seconds. This scenario is also suggestive of a low-mass seesaw mechanism to explain neutrino masses. We outline the prospects for future observations of Galactic supernovae to uncover the signals of this scenario, which could get further confirmation with additional pulsar timing array data establishing the primordial origin of the observed nano-hertz gravitational waves. Comments: 8 pages, 2 figures. Comments are welcome! Subjects: High Energy Physics - Phenomenology (hep-ph) ; Cosmology and Nongalactic Astrophysics (astro-ph.CO); High Energy Astrophysical Phenomena (astro-ph.HE) Report number: FERMILAB-PUB-25-0683-T Cite as: arXiv:2510.23713 [hep-ph] (or arXiv:2510.23713v1 [hep-ph] for this version) https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2510.23713 Focus to learn more arXiv-issued DOI via DataCite Submission history From: Anna M. Suliga [ view email ] [v1] Mon, 27 Oct 2025 18:00:03 UTC (467 KB) Full-text links: Access Paper: View a PDF of the paper titled Glimpsing Physics of Nano-Hz Gravitational Waves in Neutrinos from Core-Collapse Supernovae, by Hooman Davoudiasl and 2 other authors View PDF HTML (experimental) TeX Source view license Ancillary-file links: Ancillary files ( details ) : FOPT-SN.py IO_nu.txt IO_nubar.txt NO_nu.txt NO_nubar.txt Current browse context: hep-ph < prev | next > new | recent | 2025-10 Change to browse by: astro-ph astro-ph.CO astro-ph.HE References & Citations INSPIRE HEP NASA ADS Google Scholar Semantic Scholar export BibTeX citation Loading... BibTeX formatted citation × loading... Data provided by: Bookmark Bibliographic Tools Bibliographic and Citation Tools Bibliographic Explorer Toggle Bibliographic Explorer ( What is the Explorer? ) Connect