{"id": "1068", "question": "A multi-platform open-world dress-up adventure game developed by Papergames will have a crossover event in August 2025 with a certain company. In the promotional long-form image for the crossover published on that company's official website, what is the yellow animal located above and closest to the green character '作'?", "observations": [{"text": "PAGE_TITLE: 中国联通×《无限暖暖》联名合作即将开启！_青春_活动_后续\nPAGE_TEXT: 中国联通×《无限暖暖》联名合作即将开启！_青春_活动_后续 新闻 体育 汽车 房产 旅游 教育 时尚 科技 财经 娱乐 中国联通×《无限暖暖》联名合作即将开启！ 2025-08-14 12:01 来源: 梦幻争霸 发布于： 山西省 暖暖作伴，青春正联通 中国联通×《无限暖暖》 联名「暖暖青春卡」和「暖暖青春权益包」 即将上线！ 更多活动详情 请各位搭配师关注 中国联通与《无限暖暖》后续官方信息 返回搜狐，查看更多 平台声明：该文观点仅代表作者本人，搜狐号系信息发布平台，搜狐仅提供信息存储空间服务。 阅读 ( )", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_1", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TITLE: 《无限暖暖》官网——收集美好的开放世界\nPAGE_TEXT: 《无限暖暖》官网——收集美好的开放世界 首页 HOMEPAGE 资讯快报 NEWS DIGEST 世界观 WORLDVIEW 套装展示 SET DISPLAY 游戏特色 FEATURES 游戏攻略 GAME GUIDE 充值中心 RECHARGE CENTER 活动 《无限暖暖》携手中国联通，与你青春同行 2025-08-22 《无限暖暖》×中国联通 联名「暖暖青春卡」&「暖暖青春权益包」现已开启预约，将于9月2日正式上线，全国5所高校校园线下活动陆续展开！ 专属电话卡面、定制视频彩铃、联名家园挂饰、暖暖&大喵语音祝福...... 更多活动信息及权益说明，各位搭配师可点击长图查看~", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_2", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}], "stats": {"n_source_urls": 3, "n_image_urls": 0, "n_observations": 2}}
{"id": "1069", "question": "A paper focusing on pre-trained models in the field of Natural Language Processing, which proposed a pre-training framework with a bidirectional Transformer architecture, was published in June 2019 at the flagship conference of the North American Chapter of the Association for Computational Linguistics (NAACL). Its first author also released an extended study on this pre-trained model in July 2019 at the conference of the Association for Computational Linguistics (ACL). In Figure 7 of this paper, what is the sum of the values along the horizontal axis in the “Target domain MLM accuracy” table?", "observations": [{"text": "PAGE_TITLE: BERT: Pre-training of Deep Bidirectional Transformers for Language Understanding - ACL Anthology\nPAGE_TEXT: BERT: Pre-training of Deep Bidirectional Transformers for Language Understanding - ACL Anthology ACL Anthology News (current) FAQ (current) Corrections (current) Submissions (current) GitHub BERT : Pre-training of Deep Bidirectional Transformers for Language Understanding Jacob Devlin , Ming-Wei Chang , Kenton Lee , Kristina Toutanova Correct Metadata for Use this form to create a GitHub issue with structured data describing the correction. You will need a GitHub account. Once you create that issue, the correction will be reviewed by a staff member. ⚠️ Mobile Users: Submitting this form to create a new issue will only work with github.com, not the GitHub Mobile app. Important : The Anthology treat PDFs as authoritative. Please use this form only to correct data that is out of line with the PDF. See our corrections guidelines if you need to change the PDF. Title Adjust the title. Retain tags such as <fixed-case>. Authors Adjust author names and order to match the PDF. Add Author Abstract Correct abstract if needed. Retain XML formatting tags such as <tex-math>. You may use <b>...</b> for bold , <i>...</i> for italic , and <url>...</url> for URLs. Verification against PDF Ensure that the new title/authors match the snapshot below. (If there is no snapshot or it is too small, consult the PDF .) Authors concatenated from the text boxes above: ALL author names match the snapshot above—including middle initials, hyphens, and accents. Create GitHub issue for staff review Abstract We introduce a new language representation model called BERT, which stands for Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers. Unlike recent language representation models (Peters et al., 2018a; Radford et al., 2018), BERT is designed to pre-train deep bidirectional representations from unlabeled text by jointly conditioning on both left and right context in all layers. As a result, the pre-trained BERT model can be fine-tuned with just one additional output layer to create state-of-the-art models for a wide range of tasks, such as question answering and language inference, without substantial task-specific architecture modifications. BERT is conceptually simple and empirically powerful. It obtains new state-of-the-art results on eleven natural language processing tasks, including pushing the GLUE score to 80.5 (7.7 point absolute improvement), MultiNLI accuracy to 86.7% (4.6% absolute improvement), SQuAD v1.1 question answering Test F1 to 93.2 (1.5 point absolute improvement) and SQuAD v2.0 Test F1 to 83.1 (5.1 point absolute improvement). Anthology ID: N19-1423 Volume: Proceedings of the 2019 Conference of the North American Chapter of the Association for Computational Linguistics: Human Language Technologies, Volume 1 (Long and Short Papers) Month: June Year: 2019 Address: Minneapolis, Minnesota Editors: Jill Burstein , Christy Doran , Thamar Solorio Venue: NAACL SIG: Publisher: Association for Computational Linguistics Note: Pages: 4171–4186 Language: URL: https://aclanthology.org/N19-1423/ DOI: 10.18653/v1/N19-1423 Award: Best Long Paper Bibkey: devlin-etal-2019-bert Cite (ACL): Jacob Devlin, Ming-Wei Chang, Kenton Lee, and Kristina Toutanova. 2019. BERT: Pre-training of Deep Bidirectional Transformers for Language Understanding . In Proceedings of the 2019 Conference of the North American Chapter of the Association for Computational Linguistics: Human Language Technologies, Volume 1 (Long and Short Papers) , pages 4171–4186, Minneapolis, Minnesota. Association for Computational Linguistics. Cite (Informal): BERT: Pre-training of Deep Bidirectional Transformers for Language Understanding (Devlin et al., NAACL 2019) Copy Citation: BibTeX Markdown MODS XML Endnote More options… PDF: https://aclanthology.org/N19-1423.pdf PDF Cite Search Fix data Export citation BibTeX MODS XML Endnote Preformatted @inproceedings{devlin-etal-2019-bert, title = \"{BERT}: Pre-training of Deep Bidirectional Transformers for Language Understanding\", author = \"Devlin, Ja", "source_type": "tool_output_text", "channel_id": "source_0", "session_idx": 1, "role": "tool"}, {"text": "PAGE_TEXT: %PDF-1.3 %���� 1 0 obj > endobj 2 0 obj > endobj 3 0 obj > endobj 4 0 obj > endobj 5 0 obj > endobj 6 0 obj > endobj 7 0 obj > endobj 8 0 obj > endobj 9 0 obj > endobj 10 0 obj > endobj 11 0 obj > endobj 12 0 obj > endobj 13 0 obj > endobj 14 0 obj > stream /pdfrw_0 Do endstream endobj 15 0 obj > stream x��YK��6\u0012��W�f���\u0012\u000f���bǞ�l�\u0019{��C�\u0003F�$n(R&���_� 4\u0000� J����l�E\u0000�@�я\u000f�P l�8��ţ��@\u001b\u0007$Hi��,�,X�f��\u001a\u0007+ �\u0004q��,�d&�\u0002��(�)qP\u0006w�w�\u0017����&�\b�(\u0017�\u0007�뀦i�P\u0001�R����*�%|�T�\u0005M��^�6'q���_�of��G\u0012P\u001ae4 ����3\"\u0010�\u0013!cQ�X�\u0012 �X ު�+�J�%�z�y\u001a��\u0003C3��i\u000e�r .��bݲ�����\u000fH�S�\u0005^��-Z�a�B�òh;��k�m_Q\u0004��r��휂V���i) �\u001a���I\u0012 ��n�cO�f������:!IHDR��]'�UQm��kǰ�*ܩ�\u0003`\u0017,h�G�ȃE\u000e = ��^5�\u001b�*̮�\u0006�j>\u000f��#p\u0013& I��\u0006��\u0016�����y?��n_�V��E��bS �`&w��~ �LfEÍ갣z�x�+�T7��k� �\u000f��$\u0002е X�\u0012\u0015c�| �P�d��a\u0005��;��ͷ�v�mr�A��i\u000e둑�:%W�%� �0�mN8\u0019 �eW��\u0003\u0014W�,����\u0013�[�R�Z��Y� > /Pattern 22 0 R /ProcSet [/PDF /Text] 